<item>
            <title>[LU-406] Compile breakage in b1_8 due to unfinished patch landing.</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-406</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This patch:&lt;br/&gt;
commit fa704c0e1eea40a2370ac13938860e7648b50bdc&lt;br/&gt;
Author: Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;adilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Date:   Wed Jun 8 17:10:18 2011 -0600&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16&quot; title=&quot;Allow objects larger than 2TB in size &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-16&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-16&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; reserve OBD_CONNECT_MAXBYTES connect flag&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Reserve connect flag landed to master to prevent conflicts.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Change-Id: I9cc8ebfbfd82083085eea793eec9562d2bfb8bd8&lt;br/&gt;
    Signed-off-by: Johann Lombardi &amp;lt;johann@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Breaks b1_8 compile as it updates struct obd_connect_data without actually updating wiretest.c and pack_generic.c that try to reference now missing fields padding1 and padding2 that were replaced with padding and ocd_maxbytes&lt;/p&gt;</description>
